itioning failures. Rejection-Gate: rejected Integration because behavior text explicitly requires positions in the PR diff view, which is platform behavior.","test_description":"Against a real test PR with known multi-hunk changes, run inline-comment posting using computed anchors, then fetch created review comments from GitHub and assert each comment is anchored to the intended file and changed line in the diff. This catches off-by-one/side/path mismatches only visible with real API semantics.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Agent finds at least one real defect in a PR containing a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: pass/fail depends on model judgment quality (detecting a real defect), which stubs cannot validate. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic fake findings would always pass and hide missed-defect failures. MULTI-STEP: single model decision is sufficient; no required chain of multiple model decisions. Candidate tests: (Integration) stub model to return a defect; only tests plumbing, not detection ability. (Agentic, chosen) run real model on seeded-bug PR and assert >=1 valid defect finding references the bug region. Rejection-Gate: rejected Workflow because behavior text asks for one detection outcome, not multi-agentic-stage correctness.","test_description":"Use a benchmark PR that introduces a known bug and run the real model analysis step. Assert at least one finding correctly identifies the seeded defect class/location (with tolerant wording match). This catches real miss-detection failures from model behavior drift or prompt regressions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Each summary finding corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is run-state handoff across modules (inline posting -> summary assembly). REAL-INFRA: can be validated with in-process fakes returning comment IDs; no real OS/network required for core failure. LLM-DEP: none. MULTI-STEP agentic: none. Candidate tests: (Unit) test only summary formatter; misses cross-module ID provenance. (Integration, chosen) execute orchestration with stub poster producing deterministic IDs and assert summary entries all reference IDs emitted in this run. Rejection-Gate: rejected System because behavior text is ID correspondence logic, not external API semantics.","test_description":"Run orchestrator modules together with a fake inline-comment service that returns unique IDs per posted finding. Assert every summary item includes an ID and that each ID belongs to the set returned during this run (no stale/foreign IDs). This catches state-mismatch and provenance bugs between posting and summary construction.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped before final summary payload posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: loss can happen during module handoff/filtering between inline-findings collection and summary payload builder. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network needed to expose drop logic; deterministic in-process wiring is enough. LLM-DEP: none. MULTI-STEP agentic: none. Candidate tests: (Unit) test payload builder with static list; misses upstream orchestration drops. (Integration, chosen) run collection->transform->payload path and assert cardinality/identity preservation from inline findings to summary payload. Rejection-Gate: rejected System because behavior text targets internal payload integrity, not remote API behavior.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline stages that take posted inline findings into summary payload creation using a controlled set of findings (including edge cases like duplicates/severity variants). Assert every input finding key appears in the outgoing summary payload before post. This catches silent filtering or overwrite bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Sequence (read diff, post inline, post summary) succeeds on a real PR with fixed precomputed findings.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: explicitly requires real PR execution and real API calls in sequence. MOCK-HIDE: mocked transport would miss auth/rate-limit/schema/order failures from live platform. LLM-DEP: excluded by fixed precomputed findings. MULTI-STEP agentic: none. Candidate tests: (Integration) stub GitHub client and verify call order; catches orchestration logic only. (System, chosen) run against live test PR and assert diff read + inline posts + final summary post all succeed and are retrievable. Rejection-Gate: rejected Agentic because behavior text says fixed precomputed finding set (no model-content dependence).","test_description":"Run the automation against a real sandbox PR using a fixed findings fixture (no model call). Assert successful completion of all three external operations and verify artifacts exist on GitHub (inline comments count and one summary comment). This catches real API contract and sequencing failures.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Full live run with model-generated findings completes on a real PR without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Includes real model-generated findings plus end-to-end execution to external PR systems. LLM-DEP: yes (finding generation quality/shape). REAL-INFRA: yes (live PR API). MULTI-STEP: yes in practice as a full agent pipeline (read diff -> model analysis -> inline posting -> summary posting) where agentic output feeds later stages. Candidate tests: (Agentic) run only model analysis on real diff and assert findings exist; misses downstream execution/handoff failures. (Workflow, chosen) run full unattended pipeline and assert valid end artifacts and cross-link integrity. Rejection-Gate: rejected lower levels because behavior text explicitly requires the full live run sequence and no manual intervention.","test_description":"Execute the full production pipeline on a real test PR using the live model and live GitHub APIs. Assert run finishes without operator input, inline comments are posted, summary is posted, and summary references only IDs created in that run. This catches cross-stage failures where model output format/content breaks downstream posting or orchestration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.24,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
